"{\"uid\": \"breitbart.com-sports-2024-07-28-organizers-of-paris-olympics-apologize-parody-last-supper\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Organizers for the Paris Olympics issued an apology to people who were left offended by an LGBTQ parody of the Last Supper during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 10}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 33}, {\"ngram\": \"an apology\", \"from\": 41, \"to\": 51}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 61}, {\"ngram\": \"an LGBTQ parody\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 122}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for the Olympics opening ceremony, explained that he had \\\"wanted to send a message of love\\\" and inclusion, and did not have intentions \\\"to be subversive.\\\"\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thomas Jolly\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 165}, {\"ngram\": \"the artistic director\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 188}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 222}, {\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 271}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 279}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"intentions\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock,\\\" JollytoldtheAssociated Press.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My wish\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 353}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" JollytoldtheAssociated Press\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Most of all, I wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 494}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Last Supper display,seenduring the Olympics opening ceremony, featured Barbara Butch, a DJ, producer, and LGBTQ activist in the middle, drag queens, and transgender performers on either side of her.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 611, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper display\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 559}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"a DJ\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"producer\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"LGBTQ activist\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender performers\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"either side\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the parody of the Last Supper, the French Catholic Church's Bishops' Conference of France released a statement that the ceremony had \\\"included scenes in which Christianity was mocked and ridiculed.\\\"\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 797, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999996643614958, \"rank\": 1.5049578750924936e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8809403973181485, \"rank\": 0.13109068509560504, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9878918830776018, \"rank\": 0.012251645437414787, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"the parody\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"scenes\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 904}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This ceremony unfortunately included scenes in which Christianity was mocked and ridiculed, which we deeply regret,\\\" the organization said in itsstatement.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9878918830776018, \"rank\": 0.012251645437414787, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This ceremony\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"scenes\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"the organization\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1089}, {\"ngram\": \"itsstatement\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maria Zakharova, a spokeswoman for the Russian Foreign Ministry and the Anglican Community in Egypt also came out criticizing the Olympics for the opening ceremony, according to the outlet.\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Zakharova\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\"}, {\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"score\": 0.9999999998756266, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\"}, {\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglicanism\", \"score\": 0.7370723262692184, \"rank\": 0.35352557699160936, \"text\": \"Anglican\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglicanism\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9992692709283186, \"rank\": 0.0003392466496152965, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a spokeswoman\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlet\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group,\\\" Anne Descamps, a spokesperson f